# Next.js & React

This project uses **Next.js 16** — read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using APIs. Do not add Pages Router routes.

## Server vs client

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component — default for pages and data fetching
export default async function Page() {
  const { data } = await supabase.from("listings").select("*");
  return <ListingGrid listings={data ?? []} />;
}

// ✅ Client Component — only for interactivity
"use client";
export function CreateListingForm() { /* hooks, form submit */ }
```

- Fetch data in Server Components; pass props down.
- Add `"use client"` only for forms, hooks, or browser APIs.
- `searchParams` and route params may be Promises — await them per current Next.js docs.

## Components

- Domain types from `@/lib/types/` — do not duplicate inline.
- Props: `type FooProps = { ... }`.
- One component per file in `components/` unless tightly coupled (e.g. `EmptyListings` + `ListingCard`).
- Import via `@/*` path alias.

## Avoid

- Replacing working Server Components with client-side fetch without reason.
- New state libraries, UI frameworks, or CSS-in-JS — use Tailwind.
- Rewriting pages/components outside the current task scope.
